productTiles_20.description: Garlic has a plump bulb (or head) of individual cloves each covered with a thin skin that can be peeled. Heads of garlic can be roasted whole and the individual cloves can be crushed, chopped, pressed, pur√©ed, or sliced. Try eating fresh parsley after a meal containing garlic to help control odour.
productTiles_20.title: Colossal Garlic

productTiles_42.description: English (or hothouse) cucumbers are cylindrical green-skinned fruit with a crisp white flesh and edible seeds. English cucumbers are typically enjoyed raw and can be peeled or eaten with the skin on. Add sliced cucumber to your next vegetable platter or toss with mint and lemon juice for a refreshing salad.
productTiles_42.title: Organic English Cucumber

productTiles_27.description: Romaine (or Cos) lettuce has dark green, tightly bunched leaves with crunchy white ribs. It has a slightly bitter flavour and can be used fresh or cooked. Use romaine lettuce to make a classic Caesar salad or as a topping for burgers and sandwiches.
productTiles_27.title: Romaine Lettuce

productTiles_25.description: Baking (or russet) potatoes have a rough brown skin and a tender white flesh with a mild flavour. They are a popular variety of potato and a good choice for baking, mashing, and frying. Peel and boil russets for mashed potatoes, or bake whole and top with sour cream for a side dish for your steak or pork chops.
productTiles_25.title: Russet Potatoes 10lb Bag

productTiles_26.description: Cabbages are cruciferous vegetables that range in size, shape, and colour. Green cabbage heads have tightly wrapped leaves with a mild, spicy flavour that can be eaten raw or cooked. Shred cabbage for salad or slaw, or cut into wedges and roast with olive oil and lemon.
productTiles_26.title: Green Cabbage

productTiles_23.description: Baby (or mini) carrots are harvested young and usually very tender and sweet. Because they are already peeled, baby carrots are a quick and easy snack for people of all ages. Enjoy baby carrots on their own, add them to your vegetable platter, or roast them with a little olive oil for an easy side dish.
productTiles_23.title: Mini Carrots

productTiles_45.description: Source of fibre. Excellent source of Vitamin A
productTiles_45.title: Organic Sweet Potatoes 3lb Bag

productTiles_24.description: Bell peppers have green, orange, red, or yellow skin and a sweet flavour. They are crisp and juicy, perfect for enjoying raw with dips or hummus and to add some colour to your stir-fries.
productTiles_24.title: Greenhouse Peppers

productTiles_46.description: Yu choy sum is a relative of bok choy. It has yellowish-green stems and bright green leaves that sometimes have tiny edible yellow flowers. Yu choy sum has a similar flavour to spinach and broccoli and can be added to soups and stir-fries.
productTiles_46.title: Yu Choy Sum

productTiles_21.description: Mini cucumbers are small versions of the English variety with a bit more crunch. Mini cucumbers are typically enjoyed raw and can eaten with the skin on. Take them with you as a snack on the go or add diced mini cucumbers to your next vegetable platter or salad.
productTiles_21.title: Mini Cucumbers

productTiles_43.description: Roma (or plum) tomatoes are egg-shaped and narrow with a thick red skin and meaty texture. Because they have few seeds and a sweet flavour, Roma tomatoes are a popular choice for making tomato paste and sauce. They can also be used raw in salads or roasted for lasagna and pasta.
productTiles_43.title: Roma Tomatoes

productTiles_22.description: Sweet onions include many varieties, the most common of which is the Vidalia onion. Sweet onions have a golden yellow papery skin and white sweet flesh. They are especially good raw in salads and salsas but sweet onions can also be sliced and braised with beef or fried for onion rings.
productTiles_22.title: Sweet Onion

productTiles_44.description: Bi-colour corn has plump yellow and white kernels in tightly-spaced rows. Corn is covered with a thin layer of golden silk that should be removed prior to cooking. Cook corn and cut the kernels off the cob for salsa, salad, or chili, or boil and serve with butter for classic corn on the cob.
productTiles_44.title: Corn on the Cob, Package of 5

productTiles_0.description: English (or hothouse) cucumbers are cylindrical green-skinned fruit with a crisp white flesh and edible seeds. English cucumbers are typically enjoyed raw and can be peeled or eaten with the skin on. Add sliced cucumber to your next vegetable platter or toss with mint and lemon juice for a refreshing salad.
productTiles_0.title: English Cucumber

productTiles_30.description: Mini (or baby) carrots are harvested young and usually very tender and sweet. Because they are already peeled, baby carrots are a quick and easy snack for people of all ages. Enjoy baby carrots on their own, add them to your vegetable platter, or roast them with a little olive oil for an easy side dish.
productTiles_30.title: Carrotsmini 2Lb

productTiles_31.description: Orange bell peppers have a bright orange skin and sweet flavour. Their flesh is crisp and juicy, perfect for enjoying raw with dips or hummus. Orange bell peppers will add some colour to your stir-fry and are also perfect for grilling.
productTiles_31.title: Greenhouse Peppers, Orange

productTiles_8.description: Greenhouse tomatoes are firm and plump with a red skin when ripe. They are perfect sliced and used as a topping on burgers and sandwiches like the classic BLT. Or scoop out the pulp and seeds to make baked stuffed tomatoes.
productTiles_8.title: Tomato Beefsteak  Red

productTiles_7.description: Red bell peppers start with green skin but are left to ripen longer, giving them their bright red skin and sweet, fruity flavour. Enjoy them raw with dips or hummus, or roast red peppers to make dips and soups or as a topping for burgers and bruschetta.
productTiles_7.title: Red Peppers

productTiles_17.description: Cauliflower is a cruciferous vegetable that comes in a tight cluster of florets surrounded by crisp green leaves. It is normally white but also comes in green, purple, and orange. Add raw cauliflower florets to your next vegetable platter or roast and serve as a simple side dish with meat or fish.
productTiles_17.title: Cauliflower

productTiles_39.description: Long (or Chinese long/yard-long) beans are thin legumes that look like longer versions of green beans. They have a similar flavour to green beans but are not as crisp, and they can become mushy if overcooked. Cut long beans and add to stir-fries or saut√© and serve as a simple side dish.
productTiles_39.title: Long Beans

productTiles_6.description: *Average Vine has 3-5 Tomatoes  Vine tomatoes are typically sold in clusters attached to a fresh green vine. Because they are a little softer and juicier than other varieties, vine tomatoes are excellent when used fresh in salads, but they can also be roasted or used in many tomato-based recipes.
productTiles_6.title: Tomato on the Vine Red ( 1 Bunch)

productTiles_14.description: Zucchini are summer squash with dark to light green skin, white flesh, and tiny edible seeds. They have a delicate flavour and can be eaten raw or cooked in a variety of ways. Shred zucchini for muffins, breads, and cakes, or grill and serve as a perfect summer side dish.
productTiles_14.title: Zucchini

productTiles_36.description: Jalapeno peppers are slightly rounded chilies with smooth green skin that turns red when ripe. Jalapenos are popular because of their flavour and because they are easy to seed. Add jalapeno peppers to sauces and salsas. Scoville scale rating of 2,500 ‚Äì 8,000.
productTiles_36.title: Jalapeno Peppers

productTiles_15.description: Red (or Italian) onions have a reddish-purple papery skin and a mild sweet flavour.  Use red onions to add colour and flavour to just about any dish. Slices of raw red onion work well in salads and as a topping for burgers, or roast and serve with sausage or flank steak.
productTiles_15.title: Red Onion

productTiles_37.description: Bite-size and bursting with sweet flavour, these juicy organic grape tomatoes are great for snacking and everyday dishes. Toss in fresh salads and pasta dishes, use them to make fresh salsa or skewer for meat or veggie kebabs. They?re also delicious roasted or saut?ed as a side.
productTiles_37.title: Grape Tomatoes

productTiles_4.description: Iceberg (or crisphead) lettuce is a round, tightly-packed head of pale green leaves. It has a crisp texture and a mild flavour and is mainly used fresh. Shred iceberg lettuce for salads and slaws, or cut into wedges and drizzle with blue cheese dressing.
productTiles_4.title: Lettuce Iceberg

productTiles_12.description: Broccoli is a cruciferous vegetable that comes in a tight cluster of florets. It is deep green in colour, sometimes with a tinge of purple. Add raw broccoli florets to your next vegetable platter or pair with cheddar cheese for a quiche.
productTiles_12.title: Broccoli Crowns

productTiles_3.description: Romaine hearts are the yellowish leaves in the centre of romaine lettuce. Romaine hearts are smaller and sweeter than romaine bunches and can be enjoyed fresh or cooked. Use romaine hearts to make a classic Caesar salad or as a topping for burgers and sandwiches.
productTiles_3.title: Romaine Heart , 3 Pack

productTiles_13.description: Ginger (or gingerroot) has a tough tan skin and a fresh spicy fragrance. Ginger can be grated, slivered, or ground and its peppery flavour is used in a variety of dishes. Dried ground ginger has a very different taste and is not a suitable replacement for fresh. Peel gingerroot and add fresh to dressings and marinades, or cook in a stir-fry or soup.
productTiles_13.title: Ginger

productTiles_35.description: Yellow bell peppers have a bright yellow skin and mild, sweet flavour. Their flesh is crisp and juicy, perfect for enjoying raw with dips or hummus. Yellow bell peppers will add some colour to your stir-fry, or remove the tops and seeds to make stuffed bell peppers.
productTiles_35.title: Greenhouse Peppers, Yellow

productTiles_2.description: Celery has a cluster of pale green leaved ribs surrounding a heart (inner ribs). Trimmed celery leaves can be used as a garnish or added to a mixed greens salad. Enjoy celery on its own or with dip as a snack, or chop for soups, stews, or a¬†sandwich.
productTiles_2.title: Celery Stalks

productTiles_10.description: Green bell peppers have a bright green skin and mild, sweet flavour. Their flesh is crisp and juicy, perfect for enjoying raw with dips or hummus. Green bell peppers will add some colour to your stir-fry, or remove the tops and seeds to make stuffed bell peppers.
productTiles_10.title: Sweet Green Peppers

productTiles_32.description: Kale is a cruciferous vegetable with loosely bunched green leaves and thick centre stalks. It has a mild flavour that is similar to cabbage and becomes sweeter when cooked. Add raw kale to salads and smoothies, saut√© with lemon as a side dish, or add to soup with cannellini beans and sausage.
productTiles_32.title: Kale

productTiles_1.description: Green onions have a firm white base with a small rounded bulb and crisp bright green tops. Scallions are similar but have a straighter white base and slightly milder flavour. Chop fresh green onions for salads or pair with mushrooms for a tart or omelette.
productTiles_1.title: Green Onion

productTiles_11.description: Broccoli is a cruciferous vegetable that comes in a tight cluster of florets on top of firm, edible stalks. It is deep green in colour, sometimes with a tinge of purple. Add raw broccoli florets to your next vegetable platter or pair with cheddar cheese for a quiche.
productTiles_11.title: Broccoli

productTiles_33.description: White onions have a white papery skin and white sharp-tasting flesh. They can be used raw and hold their crunch well when cooked. Chop for salsas and chutneys, or slice and grill with bell peppers for a quick side dish to serve with steak.
productTiles_33.title: White Onion

productTiles_18.description: Sweet potatoes have a thick dark orange skin and sweet orange flesh. Yams are similar in size and shape but are not related to the sweet potato at all. Use sweet potatoes instead of regular potatoes for fries and chips or make a classic sweet potato pie.
productTiles_18.title: Sweet Potato

Because they have few seeds and a sweet flavour, Roma tomatoes are a popular choice for making tomato paste and sauce. They can also be used raw in salads or roasted for lasagna and pasta.
productTiles_9.title: Roma Tomatoes

English cucumbers are typically enjoyed raw and can be peeled or eaten with the skin on. Add sliced cucumber to your next vegetable platter or toss with mint and lemon juice for a refreshing salad.
